description: Vought F4U Corsair, WWII vintage fighter plane. I imported pics of Corsairs into autocad and modeled the plane's components to scale.  Wingspan is 15". Nose section is made of 4 ply poplar. Fuselage is made of 5 ply poplar using "lost wood technique". Wings are bent 2 ply poplar using kerf cut bending method. Tail, wheels and fuel tanks are made of poplar. Windshield is cast acrylic. Decals made using *cricut* cutter. Propellers purchased for RC airplanes.
